value: E Siberia; winters SE Asia to Philippines and Indonesia

Probably breeds in eastern Siberia; reports of its breeding in Tibet re- quire confirmation. Occurs on migration on the shores of the Sea of Okhotsk and Kamchatka; recorded from Bering Island. Winters in northeastern India, Burma, Malay Peninsula and Hainan.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: breeding requires combo of sparse larch forest for nesting, wet coastal meadows interspersed with piles of driftwood to provide shelter for the chicks, and coastal mudflats which are used for feeding;Winters estuaries, coastal mudflats, swamps

subcat_descr: Bill length (sex unknown) - Nares to tip
